  "description": [
    "Published Every Wednesday la Tabor City North Carolina Tabor City\u039b Town With A City Future By The Atlantic Publishing Co H HORACE CARTER Editor Gen Mgr KAY B WICKER Associate Editor LESTER \u0393 RUD1S1LL Business Manager \u0396 B SELLERS Asst Associate Editor S \u0388 LAYF1ELD Society Editor I Carters Column COURTS Judge Raymond Mallard spoke to the Tabor City Rotary Club last week and discussed the proposed court reform amendments to the N C Constitution that will be voted on in this Novembers general election Judge Mallard noted that some of the amendments were good and some not so good in nis opinion He was particularly in favoi of the people electing the judges rather than having them appointed But he was for the amendment that would do away with the justice of thy peace courts In this respect we think right along with him The lowest courts are generally extreme examples of abuse of pow er and few justices of the peace have the knowhow to operate a court There are hundreds 01 examples of these J \u03a1 courts try ing cases tar outside oi their jurisdiction in the State and under circumstances not even resembling the dignity that"
